<div data-live-url="/editorial/tease/9308/" class="post ">
    <h2 class="post-title"><a href="/editorial/2014/aug/14/containers?ref=tags_fiction_post_title">Containers</a></h2>
    <div class="post-details clearfix">

        <div class="post-meta">
            
            
                <span class="authors bold-upper blue"><a href="/profile/interdome/?ref=tags_fiction_post">Adam Rothstein</a> </span>
            
                <span class="blue">|</span>
                <span class="bold post-date">Thu Aug 14th, 2014 9:30 a.m.</span>
            
        </div>
        
        
            
<a class="comment-summary" href="/editorial/2014/aug/14/containers/#comments"><i class="fa fa-comment fa-lg"></i> (0)</a>

<div class="new-share">
    <a class="share-btn-cover" href="#">Share</a>

    <a class="share-btn" href="https://twitter.com/share?url=rhizome.org/editorial/2014/aug/14/containers" target="_blank"><i class="fa fa-twitter"></i></a>

    <a class="share-btn" href="http://www.tumblr.com/share/link?url=rhizome.org/editorial/2014/aug/14/containers" title="Share on Tumblr"><i class="fa fa-tumblr-square"></i></a>

    <a class="share-btn" href="#" onclick="window.open('https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=rhizome.org/editorial/2014/aug/14/containers', 'facebook-share-dialog', 'width=626,height=436'); return false;"><i class="fa fa-facebook-square"></i></a>
</div>
        
    </div>
    <hr class="black-thin"></hr>

    <div class="post-body">
        
            <p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://media.rhizome.org/blog/9308/Allan-Sekula.jpg" alt="" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: xx-small;">Allan Sekula and Noël Burch, still from <em>The Forgotten Space (</em>2010).</span></p>
<p>I woke up at the chime, looked at the mobile. New work available. I clocked in, made coffee, sat at the desk. Two hours of work right away, even before Twitter. Felt accomplished. I invoiced, and collected.</p>
<p>I met Sandra for breakfast. She's in Miami. She had the ceiling open to let in the sun. She got into a new task queue, editorial work. It's good work, she said, even though the pay isn't quite as good as advertising. What's the difference, I said, sipping my Bloody Mary. Different algorithmic authors, same algorithmic grammar problems.</p>
            
                
                    <p class="more span-15"><a href="/editorial/2014/aug/14/containers?ref=tags_fiction_post_readbtn">READ ON &raquo;</a></p>
                
            
        
        
        
